<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="EbookApp.UserGuide">
    <ContentPage.Content>

        <Grid VerticalOptions="FillAndExpand" HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" ColumnSpacing="0">
            <Grid.RowDefinitions>
                <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            </Grid.RowDefinitions>

            <StackLayout Grid.Row="0" BackgroundColor="DeepSkyBlue">
                <Label 
                        Text="User Guide"
                        Margin="10,10"
                        FontSize="20"
                        TextColor="White"
                        FontAttributes="Bold"
                        VerticalOptions="Start" />
            </StackLayout>


            <Label 
                    Grid.Row="1" 
                    Margin="10,10"
                    VerticalOptions="CenterAndExpand" 
                    HorizontalOptions="CenterAndExpand">
                <Label.Text>How to use e-Kwento?

*Import Book
>To import e-book to e-Kwento press the import button (pic. ng import)
>Select e-book genre
>Choose file from your phone press choose file button(pic. ng choose file button)
>Upload file then press ok.

*Open e-Book
>Select booklist to open then choose e-book you prefer to read.
Here you can choose between reading the e-book manually or the e-Kwento would. Read the content of the e-book for you.

•Manual Reading Mode
>Read the content of the by scrolling the phone
    •Reading Model
>Press the read/play button (pic. ng read button)

*Voice Command
>To use the voice command press the speak button (pic. ng speak button), then speak 'play or read'

*Settings
Here you can select which language to use by the e-Kwento.
>Press Choose language button then select language to use.

*Watch Related Videos
> To watch related videos of the e-book you have read press the video button (pic. ng video button) then watch videos.</Label.Text>
            </Label>

        </Grid>
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>